name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Item 1 BUSINESS Overview As our founders Larry and Sergey wrote in the original founders' letter, "Google is not a conventional company.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We do not intend to become one."

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: That unconventional spirit has been a driving force throughout our history -- inspiring us to do things like rethink the mobile device ecosystem with Android and map the world with Google Maps.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As part of that, our founders also explained that you could expect us to make "smaller bets in areas that might seem very speculative or even strange when compared to our current businesses."

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: From the start, the company has always strived to do more, and to do important and meaningful things with the resources we have.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet is a collection of businesses -- the largest of which, of course, is Google.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: It also includes businesses that are generally pretty far afield of our main Internet products such as Access, Calico, CapitalG, GV, Nest, Verily, Waymo, and X.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We report all non-Google businesses collectively as Other Bets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our Alphabet structure is about helping each of our businesses prosper through strong leaders and independence.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Access and technology for everyone The Internet is one of the world's most powerful equalizers, capable of propelling new ideas and people forward.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: At Google, our mission is to make sure that information serves everyone, not just a few.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: So whether you're a child in a rural village or a professor at an elite university, you can access the same information.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We are helping people get online by tailoring digital experiences to the needs of emerging markets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We're also making sure our core Google products are fast and useful, especially for users in areas where speed and connectivity are central concerns.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other Alphabet companies are also pursuing initiatives with similar goals.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For instance, in October 2017, Project Loon within X deployed its network of stratospheric balloons to deliver basic internet connectivity to more than 100,000 people in Puerto Rico following Hurricane Maria.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Moonshots Many companies get comfortable doing what they have always done, making only incremental changes.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This incrementalism leads to irrelevance over time, especially in technology, where change tends to be revolutionary, not evolutionary.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: People thought we were crazy when we acquired YouTube and Android and when we launched Chrome, but those efforts have matured into major platforms for digital video and mobile devices and a safer, popular browser.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to look toward the future and continue to invest for the long-term.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As we said in the original founders' letter, we will not shy away from high-risk, high-reward projects that we believe in because they are the key to our long-term success.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The power of machine learning Across the company, machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI) are increasingly driving many of our latest innovations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Within Google, our investments in machine learning over a decade have enabled us to build products that are smarter and more useful -- it's what allows you to use your voice to ask the Google Assistant for information, to translate the web from one language to another, to see better YouTube recommendations, and to search for people and events in Google Photos.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Machine learning is also showing great promise in helping us tackle big issues, like dramatically improving the energy efficiency of our data centers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Across Other Bets, machine learning helps self-driving cars better detect and respond to others on the road, and can also improve the ability of clinicians to detect diseases such as diabetic retinopathy.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google Serving our users We have always been a company committed to making big bets that have the potential to improve the lives of millions of people.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our product innovations have made our services widely used, and our brand one of the most recognized in the world.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google's core products and platforms such as Android, Chrome, Gmail, Google Maps, Google Play, Search, and YouTube each have over one billion monthly active users.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: But most important, we believe we are just beginning to scratch the surface.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our vision is to remain a place of incredible creativity and innovation that uses our technical expertise to tackle big problems.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As the majority of Alphabet's big bets continue to reside within Google, an important benefit of the shift to Alphabet has been the tremendous focus that we're able to have on Google's many extraordinary opportunities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google's mission to organize the world's information and make it universally accessible and useful has always been our North Star, and our products have come a long way since the company was founded nearly two decades ago.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Instead of just showing ten blue links in our search results, we are increasingly able to provide direct answers -- even if you're speaking your question using Voice Search -- which makes it quicker, easier and more natural to find what you're looking for.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: You can also type or talk with the Google Assistant in a conversational way across multiple devices like phones, speakers, headphones, televisions and more.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: And with Google Lens, you can now use your phone's camera to identify an unfamiliar landmark or find a trailer from a movie poster.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Over time, we have also added other services that let you access information quickly and easily -- like Google Maps, which helps you navigate to a store while showing you current traffic conditions, or Google Photos, which helps you store and organize your photos.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This drive to make information more accessible has led us over the years to improve the discovery and creation of digital content, on the web and through platforms like Google Play and YouTube.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: And with the migration to mobile, people are consuming more digital content by watching more videos, playing more games, listening to more music, reading more books, and using more apps than ever before.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Working with content creators and partners, we continue to build new ways for people around the world to find great digital content.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Fueling all of these great digital experiences are powerful platforms and hardware.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: That's why we continue to invest in platforms like our Android mobile operating system, Chrome browser, Chrome operating system, and Daydream virtual reality platform, as well as growing our family of great hardware devices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We see tremendous potential for devices to be helpful, make your life easier, and even get better over time, by combining the best of Google's AI, software, and hardware.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This is reflected in our latest generation of hardware products like the newest additions to the Google Home family called Mini and Max, Pixel 2 phone, and Pixelbook laptop.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Creating beautiful products that people rely on every day is a journey that we are investing in for the long run.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google was a company built in the cloud and has been investing in infrastructure, security, data management, analytics, and AI from the very beginning.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have continued to enhance these strengths with features like data migration, modern development environments and machine learning tools to provide enterprise-ready cloud services, including Google Cloud Platform and G Suite, to our customers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google Cloud Platform enables developers to build, test, and deploy applications on Google's highly scalable and reliable infrastructure.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our G Suite productivity tools -- which include apps like Gmail, Docs, Drive, Calendar, Hangouts, and more -- are designed with real-time collaboration and machine intelligence to help people work smarter.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Because more and more of today's great digital experiences are being built in the cloud, our Google Cloud products help businesses of all sizes take advantage of the latest technology advances to operate more efficiently.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: How we make money The goal of our advertising business is to deliver relevant ads at just the right time and to give people useful commercial information, regardless of the device they're using.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also provide advertisers with tools that help them better attribute and measure their advertising campaigns across screens.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our advertising solutions help millions of companies grow their businesses, and we offer a wide range of products across screens and formats.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generate revenues primarily by delivering both performance advertising and brand advertising.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Performance advertising creates and delivers relevant ads that users will click on, leading to direct engagement with advertisers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Most of our performance advertisers pay us when a user engages in their ads.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Performance advertising lets our advertisers connect with users while driving measurable results.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For performance advertisers, AdWords, our primary auction-based advertising program, helps create simple text-based ads that appear on Google properties and the properties of Google Network Members.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, Google Network Members use our AdSense program to display relevant ads on their properties, generating revenues when site visitors view or click on the ads.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to invest in our advertising programs and make significant upgrades.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Brand advertising helps enhance users' awareness of and affinity with advertisers' products and services, through videos, text, images, and other interactive ads that run across various devices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We help brand advertisers deliver digital videos and other types of ads to specific audiences for their brand-building marketing campaigns.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have built a world-class ad technology platform for brand advertisers, agencies, and publishers to power their digital marketing businesses.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We aim to ensure great user experiences by serving the right ads at the right time and by building deep partnerships with brands and agencies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also seek to improve the measurability of brand advertising so advertisers know when their campaigns are effective.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have allocated substantial resources to stopping bad advertising practices and protecting users on the web.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We focus on creating the best advertising experiences for our users and advertisers in many ways, ranging from filtering out invalid traffic, removing hundreds of millions of bad ads from our systems every year to closely monitoring the sites, apps, and videos where ads appear and blacklisting them when necessary to ensure that ads do not fund bad content.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Beyond our advertising business, we also generate revenues in other areas, such as digital content, enterprise cloud services, and hardware.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other Bets Throughout Alphabet, we are also using technology to try and solve big problems across many industries.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet's Other Bets are early-stage businesses, and our goal is for them to become thriving, successful businesses in the medium to long term.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: To do this, we make sure we have a strong CEO to run each company while also rigorously handling capital allocation and working to make sure each business is executing well.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: While these early-stage businesses naturally come with considerable uncertainty, some of them are already generating revenue and making important strides in their industries.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For instance, Nest recently expanded its connected home product line by introducing the Nest Thermostat E and a new home security solution that includes the Nest Hello video doorbell, Nest Cam IQ outdoor security camera, and the Nest Secure alarm system.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our self-driving car company, Waymo, continues to progress the development and testing of its technology and now has a fleet of vehicles in Phoenix, Arizona, driving without a person behind the wheel.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Life sciences company Verily has also made significant progress on key programs, like the launch of its Project Baseline study with Duke University and Stanford Medicine, and received an $800 million investment in 2017 from Temasek to accelerate its strategic programs.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to build these businesses thoughtfully and systematically to capitalize on the opportunities ahead.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We are investing for the long term while being very deliberate about the focus, scale and pace of investments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generate revenues from internet and TV services, licensing and R&D services, and Nest branded hardware.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Competition Our business is characterized by rapid change as well as new and disruptive technologies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We face formidable competition in every aspect of our business, particularly from companies that seek to connect people with online information and provide them with relevant advertising.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We face competition from:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • General purpose search engines and information services, such as Baidu, Microsoft's Bing, Naver, Seznam, Verizon's Yahoo, and Yandex.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Vertical search engines and e-commerce websites, such as Amazon and eBay (e-commerce), Kayak (travel queries), LinkedIn (job queries), and WebMD (health queries). Some users will navigate directly to such content, websites, and apps rather than go through Google.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Social networks, such as Facebook, Snap, and Twitter. Some users increasingly rely on social networks for product or service referrals, rather than seeking information through traditional search engines.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Other forms of advertising, such as billboards, magazines, newspapers, radio, and television. Our advertisers typically advertise in multiple media, both online and offline.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Other online advertising platforms and networks, including Amazon, AppNexus, Criteo, and Facebook, that compete for advertisers that use AdWords, our primary auction-based advertising platform.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Providers of digital video services, such as Amazon, Facebook, Hulu, and Netflix.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Companies that design, manufacture, and market consumer electronics products, including businesses that have developed proprietary platforms.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Providers of enterprise cloud services, including Alibaba, Amazon, and Microsoft.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Digital assistant providers, such as Amazon, Apple, and Microsoft.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Competing successfully in our advertising-related businesses depends heavily on our ability to deliver and distribute innovative products and technologies to the marketplace so that we can attract and retain:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Users, for whom other products and services are literally one click away, primarily on the basis of the relevance and usefulness of our search results and the features, availability, and ease of use of our products and services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Advertisers, primarily based on our ability to generate sales leads, and ultimately customers, and to deliver their advertisements in an efficient and effective manner across a variety of distribution channels.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Content providers, primarily based on the quality of our advertiser base, our ability to help these partners generate revenues from advertising, and the terms of our agreements with them.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Intellectual Property We rely on various intellectual property laws, confidentiality procedures and contractual provisions to protect our proprietary technology and our brand.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have registered, and applied for the registration of, U.S. and international trademarks, service marks, domain names and copyrights.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have also filed patent applications in the U.S. and foreign countries covering certain of our technology, and acquired patent assets to supplement our portfolio.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have licensed in the past, and expect that we may license in the future, certain of our rights to other parties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Culture and Employees We take great pride in our culture.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We embrace collaboration and creativity, and encourage the iteration of ideas to address complex technical challenges.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Transparency and open dialogue are central to how we work, and we like to ensure that company news reaches our employees first through internal channels.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Despite our rapid growth, we still cherish our roots as a startup and wherever possible empower employees to act on great ideas regardless of their role or function within the company.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We strive to hire great employees, with backgrounds and perspectives as diverse as those of our global users.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We work to provide an environment where these talented people can have fulfilling careers addressing some of the biggest challenges in technology and society.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our employees are among our best assets and are critical for our continued success.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We expect to continue investing in hiring talented employees and to provide competitive compensation programs to our employees.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As of December 31, 2017, we had 80,110 full-time employees.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Although we have work councils and statutory employee representation obligations in certain countries, our U.S. employees are not represented by a labor union.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Competition for qualified personnel in our industry is intense, particularly for software engineers, computer scientists, and other technical staff.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Seasonality Our business is affected by seasonal fluctuations in Internet usage, advertising expenditures, and underlying business trends such as traditional retail seasonality.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other Items Climate change is one of the most significant global challenges of our time, and we've long been committed to improving our energy consumption.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In 2012, we set a goal to reach 100% renewable energy for our operations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: While we are still performing final analysis for the year, in 2017, we purchased a total wind and solar capacity of about three gigawatts, which we expect will be enough renewables to match the energy consumption of our global operations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to invest in our existing products and services as well as developing new products and services through research and product development.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We often release early-stage products.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We then use data and user feedback to decide if and how to invest further in those products.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Research and development expenses include the vast majority of engineering and technical headcount responsible for research and development of our existing and new products and services, as well as their associated costs.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For more information, please refer to the Consolidated Statements of Income included in Part II of this Annual Report on Form 10-K.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For information about segments and geographic areas, please refer to Note 15 of the Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements included in Part II of this Annual Report on Form 10-K.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As part of the Alphabet reorganization, we converted Google Inc. into a limited liability company in September 2017.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: You can get information on the operation of the Public Reference Room by calling the SEC at 1-800-SEC-0330.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We webcast via our investor relations website our earnings calls and certain events we participate in or host with members of the investment community.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our investor relations website also provides notifications of news or announcements regarding our financial performance, including SEC filings, investor events, press and earnings releases, and blogs.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Item 1A RISK FACTORS Our operations and financial results are subject to various risks and uncertainties, including but not limited to those described below, which could adversely affect our business, financial condition, results of operations, cash flows, and the trading price of our common and capital stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Risks Related to Our Businesses and Industries We face intense competition.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If we do not continue to innovate and provide products and services that are useful to users, we may not remain competitive, and our revenues and operating results could be adversely affected.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our businesses are rapidly evolving, intensely competitive, and subject to changing technologies, shifting user needs, and frequent introductions of new products and services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Competing successfully depends heavily on our ability to accurately anticipate technology developments and deliver innovative, relevant and useful products, services, and technologies to the marketplace in a timely manner.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As our businesses evolve, the competitive pressure to innovate will encompass a wider range of products and services, including products and services that may be outside of our historical core business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, we must continue to invest significant resources in research and development, including through acquisitions, in order to enhance our technology and our existing products and services, and introduce new products and services that people can easily and effectively use.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have many competitors in different industries.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our current and potential domestic and international competitors range from large and established companies to emerging start-ups.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Some companies have longer operating histories and more established relationships with customers and users.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: They can use their experiences and resources in ways that could affect our competitive position, including by making acquisitions, continuing to invest heavily in research and development and in hiring talent, aggressively initiating intellectual property claims (whether or not meritorious), and continuing to compete aggressively for users, advertisers, and content providers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Emerging start-ups may be able to innovate and provide products and services faster than we can or may foresee the consumer need for products and services before us.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, new products and services can sometimes present new and difficult technological and legal challenges, which may negatively impact our brands and demand for our products and services and adversely impact our revenues and operating results.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our operating results would also suffer if our innovations are not responsive to the needs of our users, advertisers, and content providers; are not appropriately timed with market opportunities; or are not effectively brought to market.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As technologies continue to develop, our competitors may be able to offer user experiences that are, or that are seen to be, substantially similar to or better than ours.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This may force us to compete in different ways and expend significant resources in order to remain competitive.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If our competitors are more successful than we are in developing compelling products or in attracting and retaining users, advertisers, and content providers, our revenues and operating results could be adversely affected.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generate substantially all of our revenues from advertising, and reduced spending by advertisers or a loss of partners could harm our advertising business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generated over 86% of total revenues from advertising in 2017.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Many of our advertisers, companies that distribute our products and services, digital publishers, and content partners can terminate their contracts with us at any time.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Those partners may not continue to do business with us if we do not create more value (such as increased numbers of users or customers, new sales leads, increased brand awareness, or more effective monetization) than their available alternatives.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If we do not provide superior value or deliver advertisements efficiently and competitively, we could see a decrease in revenue and other adverse impacts to our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, expenditures by advertisers tend to be cyclical, reflecting overall economic conditions and budgeting and buying patterns.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Adverse macroeconomic conditions can also have a material negative impact on user activity and the demand for advertising and cause our advertisers to reduce the amounts they spend on advertising, which could adversely affect our revenues and advertising business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our ongoing investment in new businesses and new products, services, and technologies is inherently risky, and could disrupt our current operations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have invested and expect to continue to invest in new businesses, products, services, and technologies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The creation of Alphabet as a holding company in 2015 and the investments that we are making across various areas in Google and Other Bets are a reflection of our ongoing efforts to innovate and provide products and services that are useful to users.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Such endeavors may involve significant risks and uncertainties, including insufficient revenues from such investments to offset any new liabilities assumed and expenses associated with these new investments, inadequate return of capital on our investments, distraction of management from current operations, use of alternative investment or compensation structures, and unidentified issues not discovered in our due diligence of such strategies and offerings that could cause us to fail to realize the anticipated benefits of such investments and incur unanticipated liabilities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Because these new ventures are inherently risky, no assurance can be given that such strategies and offerings will be successful and will not adversely affect our reputation, financial condition, and operating results.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The Internet is accessed through a variety of platforms and form factors that continue to evolve with the advancement of technology and user preferences.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If manufacturers and users do not widely adopt versions of our search technology, products, or operating systems developed for these devices and modalities, our business could be adversely affected.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The number of people who access the Internet through devices other than desktop computers, including mobile phones, smartphones, laptops and tablets, video game consoles, voice-assisted speakers, automobiles, and television set-top devices, is increasing dramatically.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The functionality and user experience associated with some alternative devices and modalities may make the use of our products and services or the generation of advertising revenue through such devices more difficult (or just different), and the versions of our products and services developed for these devices may not be compatible or compelling to users, manufacturers, or distributors of alternative devices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Each manufacturer or distributor may establish unique technical standards for its devices, and our products and services may not work or be viewable on these devices as a result.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Some manufacturers may also elect not to include our products on their devices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, search queries are increasingly being undertaken via apps tailored to particular devices or social media platforms, which could affect our search and advertising business over time.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As new devices and platforms are continually being released, it is difficult to predict the problems we may encounter in adapting our products and services and developing competitive new products and services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We expect to continue to devote significant resources to the creation, support, and maintenance of products and services across multiple platforms and devices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If we are unable to attract and retain a substantial number of alternative device manufacturers, suppliers, distributors, developers, and users to our products and services, or if we are slow to develop products and technologies that are more compatible with alternative devices and platforms, we will fail to capture the opportunities available as consumers and advertisers continue to exist in a dynamic, multi-platform environment.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our revenue growth rate could decline over time, and we anticipate downward pressure on our operating margin in the future.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our revenue growth rate could decline over time as a result of a number of factors, including:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • increasing competition, • changes in device mix, geographic mix, ongoing product and policy changes, product mix, and property mix,

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • the challenges in maintaining our growth rate as our revenues increase to higher levels,

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • the evolution of the online advertising market, including the increasing variety of online platforms for advertising, and the other markets in which we participate, and

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • the rate of user adoption of our products, services, and technologies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We believe our margins could experience downward pressure as a result of increasing competition and increased costs for many aspects of our business as well as the continuing shift to mobile, changes in device mix, and the contribution of new businesses to overall revenue.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For instance, the margin on revenues we generate from our Google Network Members is significantly less than the margin on revenues we generate from advertising on Google properties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Consequently, our margins will experience downward pressure if a greater percentage of our revenues comes from ads placed on our Google Network Members' properties compared to revenues generated through ads placed on Google properties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, the margin we earn on revenues generated from our Google Network Members could decrease in the future if we pay an even larger percentage of advertising fees to our Google Network Members.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Furthermore, in our multi-device world, we generate our advertising revenues increasingly from mobile and newer advertising formats, and the margins from the advertising revenues from these sources have generally been lower than those from traditional desktop search.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also expect our TAC paid to our distribution partners to increase due to changes in device mix between mobile, desktop, and tablet, partner mix, partner agreement terms, and the percentage of queries channeled through paid access points.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, our margins could experience downward pressure as revenues from the sale of hardware products and cloud-based services increase as a percentage of consolidated revenues because the margin on the sale of these products and services have generally been lower than that from Google search.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Furthermore, our margins could be impacted adversely if we spend a proportionately larger amount to promote new products and services or distribute certain products or if we invest more heavily in our innovation efforts across the Company (such as our Other Bets businesses) than we have historically.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We are subject to increasing regulatory scrutiny that may negatively impact our business. Additionally, changes in public policies governing a wide range of topics may adversely affect our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The growth of our company and our expansion into a variety of new fields involves a variety of new regulatory issues, and we have experienced increased regulatory scrutiny as we have grown.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For instance, various regulatory agencies are reviewing aspects of our search and other businesses, which can lead to increased scrutiny from other regulators and legislators, that may affect our reputation, brand and third-party relationships.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Such reviews may also result in substantial regulatory fines, changes to our business practices and other penalties, which could negatively impact our business and results of operations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to cooperate with the European Commission and other regulatory authorities around the world in investigations they are conducting with respect to our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, changes in social, political, and regulatory conditions or in laws and policies governing a wide range of topics may disrupt our business practices. These changes could negatively impact our business and results of operations in material ways.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: A variety of new and existing laws could subject us to claims or otherwise harm our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We are subject to numerous U.S. and international laws and regulations covering a wide variety of subject matters.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: New laws and regulations (or new interpretations of existing laws and regulations) may make our products and services less useful, require us to incur substantial costs, expose us to unanticipated civil or criminal liability, or cause us to change our business practices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For example, current and new patent laws such as U.S. patent laws and European patent laws may affect the ability of companies, including us, to protect their innovations and defend against claims of patent infringement.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Similarly, changes to copyright laws being considered in Europe and elsewhere may increase costs or require companies, including us, to change or cease offering certain existing services.

name: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Claims have been, or may be, threatened and filed against us under both U.S. and international laws for defamation, invasion of privacy and other tort claims, unlawful activity, patent, copyright and trademark infringement, product liability, or other theories based on the nature and content of the materials searched and the ads posted by our users, our products and services, or content generated by our users.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Furthermore, many of these laws do not contemplate or address the unique issues raised by a number of our new businesses, products, services and technologies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other laws that could subject us to claims or otherwise harm our business include, among others:

sentence: • We rely on statutory safe harbors, as set forth in the Digital Millennium Copyright Act in the United States and the E-Commerce Directive in Europe, against copyright liability for various linking, caching, and hosting activities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Any legislation or court rulings impacting these safe harbors may adversely impact us.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • The General Data Protection Regulation, coming into effect in the European Union in May of 2018, which creates a range of new compliance obligations, which could cause us to change our business practices, and will increase financial penalties for noncompliance significantly.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Court decisions such as the judgment of the Court of Justice of the European Union on May 13, 2014 on the 'right to be forgotten,' which allows individuals to demand that Google remove search results about them in certain instances, may limit the content we can show to our users and impose significant operational burdens.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Court decisions that require Google to suppress content not just in the jurisdiction of the issuing court, but for all of our users worldwide, including locations where the content at issue is lawful.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The Supreme Court of Canada issued such a decision against Google in June 2017, and others could treat its decision as persuasive.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For instance, with respect to the 'right to be forgotten,' a follow-up case is pending before the Court of Justice of the European Union, which could result in an order to apply delisting actions under the 'right to be forgotten' worldwide.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Various U.S. and international laws that restrict the distribution of materials considered harmful to children and impose additional restrictions on the ability of online services to collect information from minors.

name: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Data protection laws passed by many states within the U.S. and by certain countries that require notification to users when there is a security breach of personal data.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Data localization laws, which generally mandate that certain types of data collected in a particular country be stored and/or processed within that country.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Privacy laws, which could be interpreted over-broadly to limit some product offerings and increase costs.

name: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The GDPR will create a range of new compliance obligations, which could cause us to change our business practices, and will significantly increase financial penalties for noncompliance (including possible fines of up to 4% of global annual turnover for the preceding financial year or €20 million (whichever is higher) for the most serious infringements).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, the European Commission in July 2016 and the Swiss Government in January 2017 approved the EU-U.S. and the Swiss-U.S. Privacy Shield frameworks, respectively, which are designed to allow U.S. companies that self-certify to the U.S. Department of Commerce and publicly commit to comply with the Privacy Shield requirements to freely import personal data from the EU and Switzerland.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We face a number of manufacturing and supply chain risks that, if not properly managed, could adversely impact our financial results and prospects.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We face a number of risks related to manufacturing and supply chain management. These manufacturing and supply chain risks could impact our ability to supply both our products and our internet-based services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We rely on third parties to manufacture many of our assemblies and finished products, third-party arrangements for the design of some components and parts, and third party distributors, including cellular network carriers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our business could be negatively affected if we are not able to engage third parties with the necessary capabilities or capacity on reasonable terms, or if those we engage fail to meet their obligations (whether due to financial difficulties or other reasons), or make adverse changes in the pricing or other material terms of our arrangements with them.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have in the past, and may experience in the future, supply shortages and price increases driven by raw material availability, manufacturing capacity, labor shortages, industry allocations, natural disasters and significant changes in the financial or business condition of our suppliers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We may experience shortages or other supply chain disruptions in the future that could negatively impact our operations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, some of the components we use in our technical infrastructure and products are available only from a single source or limited sources, and we may not be able to find replacement vendors on favorable terms or at all in the event of a supply chain disruption.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, a significant hardware supply interruption could delay critical data center upgrades or expansions.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We may enter into long term contracts that commit us to significant terms and conditions of supply.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We may be liable for material and product that is not consumed due to market acceptance, technological change, obsolescences, quality, product recalls, and warranty issues.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For instance, because many of our hardware supply contracts have volume-based pricing or minimum purchase requirements, if the volume of our hardware sales decreases or does not reach projected targets, we could face increased materials and manufacturing costs or other financial liabilities that could make our products more costly per unit to manufacture and therefore less competitive and negatively impact our financial results.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Furthermore, certain of our competitors may negotiate more favorable contractual terms based on volume and other commitments that may provide them with competitive advantages and may impact our supply.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, the products and services we sell or offer may have quality issues resulting from the design or manufacture of the product, or from the software used.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Sometimes, these issues may be caused by components we purchase from other manufacturers or suppliers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If the quality of our products and services does not meet our customers' expectations or our products or services are found to be defective, then our sales and operating earnings, and ultimately our reputation, could be negatively impacted.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also require our suppliers and business partners to comply with law and, where applicable, our company policies regarding workplace and employment practices, data security, environmental compliance and intellectual property licensing, but we do not control them or their practices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If any of them violates laws or implements practices regarded as unethical, we could experience supply chain disruptions, canceled orders, terminations of or damage to key relationships, and damage to our reputation.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If any of them fails to procure necessary license rights to third-party intellectual property, legal action could ensue that could impact the saleability of our products and expose us to financial obligations to third parties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act includes disclosure requirements regarding the use of certain minerals mined from the Democratic Republic of Congo and adjoining countries (DRC) and procedures pertaining to a manufacturer's efforts regarding the source of such minerals.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: SEC rules implementing these requirements may have the effect of reducing the pool of suppliers who can supply DRC conflict free components and parts, and we may not be able to obtain DRC conflict free products or supplies in sufficient quantities for our operations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Since our supply chain is complex, we may face reputational challenges with our customers, stockholders and other stakeholders if we are unable to sufficiently verify the origins for the minerals used in our products.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Web spam and content farms could decrease our search quality, which could damage our reputation and deter our current and potential users from using our products and services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Web spam refers to websites that attempt to violate a search engine's quality guidelines or that otherwise seek to rank higher in search results than a search engine's assessment of their relevance and utility would rank them.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Although English-language web spam in our search results has been significantly reduced, and web spam in most other languages is limited, we expect web spammers will continue to seek ways to improve their rankings inappropriately.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continuously combat web spam, including through indexing technology that makes it harder for spam-like, less useful web content to rank highly.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We face challenges from low-quality and irrelevant content websites, including content farms, which are websites that generate large quantities of low-quality content to help them improve their search rankings.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We are continually launching algorithmic changes focused on low-quality websites.

name: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, as we continue to take actions to improve our search quality and reduce low-quality content, this may in the short run reduce our Google Network Members' revenues, since some of these websites are Google Network Members.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Interruption or failure of our information technology and communications systems could hurt our ability to effectively provide our products and services, which could damage our reputation and harm our operating results.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The availability of our products and services depends on the continuing operation of our information technology and communications systems.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our systems are vulnerable to damage or interruption from earthquakes, terrorist attacks, natural disasters, the effects of climate change (such as sea level rise, drought, flooding, wildfires, and increased storm severity), power loss, telecommunications failures, computer viruses, computer denial of service attacks, or other attempts to harm our systems.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Some of our data centers are located in areas with a high risk of major earthquakes or other natural disasters.

name: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Some of our systems are not fully redundant, and our disaster recovery planning cannot account for all eventualities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The occurrence of a natural disaster, a decision to close a facility we are using, or other unanticipated problems at our data centers could result in lengthy interruptions in our service.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, our products and services are highly technical and complex and may contain errors or vulnerabilities, which could result in interruptions in our services or the failure of our systems.

sentence: Our international operations expose us to additional risks that could harm our business, operating results, and financial condition.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our international operations are significant to our revenues and net income, and we plan to continue to grow internationally.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: International revenues accounted for approximately 53% of our consolidated revenues in 2017.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In certain international markets, we have limited operating experience and may not succeed.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition to risks described elsewhere in this section, our international operations expose us to other risks, including the following:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Restrictions on foreign ownership and investments, and stringent foreign exchange controls that might prevent us from repatriating cash earned in countries outside the U.S.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Import and export requirements, tariffs, trade disputes and barriers, and customs classifications that may prevent us from offering products or providing services to a particular market and may increase our operating costs.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Longer payment cycles in some countries, increased credit risk, and higher levels of payment fraud.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Evolving foreign laws and legal systems.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Uncertainty regarding liability for services and content, including uncertainty as a result of local laws and lack of legal precedent.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Different employee/employer relationships, existence of workers' councils and labor unions, and other challenges caused by distance, language, and cultural differences, making it harder to do business in certain jurisdictions.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, changes in international local political, economic, regulatory, tax, social, and labor conditions may adversely harm our business, and compliance with complex international and U.S. laws and regulations that apply to our international operations increases our cost of doing business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These numerous and sometimes conflicting laws and regulations include, among others, internal control and disclosure rules, privacy and data protection requirements, anti-corruption laws, such as the U.S. Foreign Corrupt Practices Act, and other local laws prohibiting corrupt payments to governmental officials, and competition regulations, among others.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Violations of these laws and regulations could result in fines and penalties, criminal sanctions against us, our officers, or our employees, prohibitions on the conduct of our business and on our ability to offer our products and services in one or more countries, and could also materially affect our brand, our international growth efforts, our ability to attract and retain employees, our business, and our operating results.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Although we have implemented policies and procedures designed to ensure compliance with these laws and regulations, there can be no assurance that our employees, contractors, or agents will not violate our policies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Finally, since we conduct business in currencies other than U.S. dollars but report our financial results in U.S. dollars, we face exposure to fluctuations in foreign currency exchange rates.

sentence: Although we hedge a portion of our international currency exposure, significant fluctuations in exchange rates between the U.S. dollar and foreign currencies may adversely affect our revenues and earnings.

sentence: Some of these providers have taken, or have stated that they may take measures, including legal actions, that could degrade, disrupt, or increase the cost of user access to certain of our products by restricting or prohibiting the use of their infrastructure to support or facilitate our offerings, or by charging increased fees to us or our users to provide our offerings.

sentence: Some jurisdictions have adopted regulations prohibiting certain forms of discrimination by Internet access providers, but there is substantial uncertainty in the United States and elsewhere regarding such protections.

name: Alphabet Inc.

sentence: New and existing technologies could block ads online, which would harm our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We could be subject to changes in tax rates, the adoption of new U.S. or international tax legislation, or exposure to additional tax liabilities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our future income taxes could be adversely affected by earnings being lower than anticipated in jurisdictions that have lower statutory tax rates and higher than anticipated in jurisdictions that have higher statutory tax rates, the net gains and losses recognized by legal entities on certain hedges and related hedged intercompany and other transactions under our foreign exchange risk management program, changes in the valuation of our deferred tax assets or liabilities, or changes in tax laws, regulations, or accounting principles, as well as certain discrete items.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, we are subject to regular review and audit by both domestic and foreign tax authorities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, we have received, and may in the future receive, assessments in multiple jurisdictions on various tax-related assertions, including transfer pricing adjustments or permanent establishment.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Any adverse outcome of such a review or audit could have a negative effect on our operating results and financial condition.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, the determination of our worldwide provision for income taxes and other tax liabilities requires significant judgment, and there are many transactions and calculations where the ultimate tax determination is uncertain.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Although we believe our estimates are reasonable, the ultimate tax outcome may differ from the amounts recorded in our financial statements and may materially affect our financial results in the period or periods for which such determination is made.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Furthermore, due to shifting economic and political conditions, tax policies, laws or rates in various jurisdictions may be subject to significant change, which could materially affect our financial position and results of operations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The ongoing effects of the Tax Act and the refinement of provisional estimates could make our results difficult to predict.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our effective tax rate may fluctuate in the future as a result of the Tax Act, which was enacted on December 22, 2017.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The Tax Act introduces significant changes to U.S. income tax law that will have a meaningful impact on our provision for income taxes.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Accounting for the income tax effects of the Tax Act requires significant judgments and estimates in the interpretation and calculations of the provisions of the Tax Act.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Due to the timing of the enactment and the complexity involved in applying the provisions of the Tax Act, we made reasonable estimates of the effects and recorded provisional amounts in our financial statements for the year ended December 31, 2017.

sentence: The U.S. Treasury Department, the Internal Revenue Service (IRS), and other standard-setting bodies may issue guidance on how the provisions of the Tax Act will be applied or otherwise administered that is

sentence: As we collect and prepare necessary data, and interpret the Tax Act and any additional guidance issued by the IRS or other standard-setting bodies, we may make adjustments to the provisional amounts that could materially affect our financial position and results of operations as well as our effective tax rate in the period in which the adjustments are made.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Risks Related to Ownership of Our Stock The trading price for our Class A common stock and non-voting Class C capital stock may continue to be volatile.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The trading price of our stock has at times experienced substantial price volatility and may continue to be volatile.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For example, from January 1, 2017 through December 31, 2017, the closing price of our Class A common stock ranged from $807.77 per share to $1,085.09 per share, and the closing price of our Class C capital stock ranged from $786.14 to $1,077.14 per share.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition to the factors discussed in this Annual Report on Form 10-K, the trading price of our Class A common stock and Class C capital stock may fluctuate widely in response to various factors, many of which are beyond our control, including, among others:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Quarterly variations in our results of operations or those of our competitors.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Announcements by us or our competitors of acquisitions, divestitures, investments, new products, significant contracts, commercial relationships, or capital commitments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Recommendations by securities analysts or changes in earnings estimates.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Announcements about our earnings that are not in line with analyst expectations, the risk of which is enhanced because it is our policy not to give guidance on earnings.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Announcements by our competitors of their earnings that are not in line with analyst expectations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Commentary by industry and market professionals about our products, strategies, and other matters affecting our business and results, regardless of its accuracy.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • The volume of shares of Class A common stock and Class C capital stock available for public sale.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Sales of Class A common stock and Class C capital stock by us or by our stockholders (including sales by our directors, executive officers, and other employees).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Short sales, hedging, and other derivative transactions on shares of our Class A common stock and Class C capital stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • The perceived values of Class A common stock and Class C capital stock relative to one another.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our share repurchase program.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, the stock market in general, which can be impacted by various factors, including overall economic and political conditions, and the market for technology companies in particular, have experienced extreme price and volume fluctuations that have often been unrelated or disproportionate to the operating performance of those companies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These broad market and industry factors may harm the market price of our Class A common stock and our Class C capital stock regardless of our actual operating performance.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We cannot guarantee that our share repurchase program will be fully consummated or that our share repurchase program will enhance long-term stockholder value, and share repurchases could increase the volatility of the price of our stock and could diminish our cash reserves.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In October 2016, our board of directors authorized our company to repurchase up to $7,019,340,976.83 of our Class C capital stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In January 2018, our board of directors authorized the repurchase of up to an additional$8,589,869,056 of our Class C capital stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The repurchase program does not have an expiration date.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The share repurchase program, authorized by our board of directors, does not obligate Alphabet to repurchase any specific dollar amount or to acquire any specific number of shares.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The share repurchase program could affect the price of our stock and increase volatility and may be suspended or terminated at any time, which may result in a decrease in the trading price of our stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The concentration of our stock ownership limits our stockholders' ability to influence corporate matters.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our Class B common stock has 10 votes per share, our Class A common stock has one vote per share, and our Class C capital stock has no voting rights.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As of December 31, 2017, Larry, Sergey, and Eric E. Schmidt beneficially owned approximately 92.7% of our outstanding Class B common stock, which represented approximately 56.7% of

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: the voting power of our outstanding capital stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Larry, Sergey, and Eric therefore have significant influence over management and affairs and over all matters requiring stockholder approval, including the election of directors and significant corporate transactions, such as a merger or other sale of our company or our assets, for the foreseeable future.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, because our Class C capital stock carries no voting rights (except as required by applicable law), the issuance of the Class C capital stock, including in future stock-based acquisition transactions and to fund employee equity incentive programs, could prolong the duration of Larry and Sergey's current relative ownership of our voting power and their ability to elect all of our directors and to determine the outcome of most matters submitted to a vote of our stockholders.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Together with Eric, they would also continue to be able to control any required stockholder vote with respect to certain change in control transactions involving Alphabet (including an acquisition of Alphabet by another company).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This concentrated control limits or severely restricts our stockholders' ability to influence corporate matters and, as a result, we may take actions that our stockholders do not view as beneficial.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, the market price of our Class A common stock and our Class C capital stock could be adversely affected.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Provisions in our charter documents and under Delaware law could discourage a takeover that stockholders may consider favorable.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Provisions in Alphabet's certificate of incorporation and bylaws may have the effect of delaying or preventing a change of control or changes in our management. These provisions include the following:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our certificate of incorporation provides for a tri-class capital stock structure.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result of this structure, Larry, Sergey, and Eric have significant influence over all matters requiring stockholder approval, including the election of directors and significant corporate transactions, such as a merger or other sale of our company or our assets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This concentrated control could discourage others from initiating any potential merger, takeover, or other change of control transaction that other stockholders may view as beneficial.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As noted above, the issuance of the Class C capital stock could have the effect of prolonging the influence of Larry, Sergey, and Eric.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our board of directors has the right to elect directors to fill a vacancy created by the expansion of the board of directors or the resignation, death, or removal of a director, which prevents stockholders from being able to fill vacancies on our board of directors.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our stockholders may not act by written consent. As a result, a holder, or holders, controlling a majority of our capital stock would not be able to take certain actions without holding a stockholders' meeting.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our certificate of incorporation prohibits cumulative voting in the election of directors. This limits the ability of minority stockholders to elect director candidates.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Stockholders must provide advance notice to nominate individuals for election to the board of directors or to propose matters that can be acted upon at a stockholders' meeting.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These provisions may discourage or deter a potential acquirer from conducting a solicitation of proxies to elect the acquirer's own slate of directors or otherwise attempting to obtain control of our company.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our board of directors may issue, without stockholder approval, shares of undesignated preferred stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The ability to issue undesignated preferred stock makes it possible for our board of directors to issue preferred stock with voting or other rights or preferences that could impede the success of any attempt to acquire us.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a Delaware corporation, we are also subject to certain Delaware anti-takeover provisions.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Under Delaware law, a corporation may not engage in a business combination with any holder of 15% or more of its outstanding voting stock unless the holder has held the stock for three years or, among other things, the board of directors has approved the transaction.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our board of directors could rely on Delaware law to prevent or delay an acquisition of us.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Risks Related to Our Holding Company Reorganization As a holding company, Alphabet is dependent on the operations and funds of its subsidiaries.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On October 2, 2015, we completed a reorganization pursuant to which Alphabet became a holding company with no business operations of its own.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet's only significant assets are the outstanding equity interests in its subsidiaries, including Google.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, we rely on cash flows from subsidiaries to meet our obligations, including to service any debt obligations of Alphabet.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We may not obtain the anticipated benefits of our reorganization into a holding company structure.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We believe that our holding company reorganization and the current operating structure increases management scale and allows us to focus on running our diverse businesses independently with the goal of maximizing each business' potential.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The benefits of this reorganization may not be obtained if circumstances prevent us from taking

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: advantage of the strategic and business opportunities that we expect it may afford us.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, we may incur the costs of a holding company structure without realizing the benefits, which could adversely affect our reputation, financial condition, and operating results.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet's management is dedicating significant effort to the Other Bets' operating structures and business operations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These efforts may divert management's focus and resources from Alphabet's overall business, corporate initiatives, or strategic opportunities, which could have an adverse effect on our businesses, results of operations, financial condition, or prospects.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, our subsidiaries may be restricted in their ability to pay cash dividends or to make other distributions to Alphabet, as the new holding company.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Trends in Our Business The following trends have contributed to the results of our consolidated operations, and we anticipate that they will continue to impact our future results:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: •Users' behaviors and advertising continue to shift online as the digital economy evolves.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The continuing shift from an offline to online world has contributed to the growth of our business since inception, resulting in increasing revenues, and we expect that this online shift will continue to benefit our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: •As online advertising evolves, we continue to expand our product offerings which may impact our monetization.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As interactions between users and advertisers change and as online user behavior evolves, we continue to expand and evolve our product offerings to serve their changing needs.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Over time, we expect our monetization trends to fluctuate.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For example, we have seen an increase in YouTube engagement ads, which monetize at a lower rate than traditional desktop search ads.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, we continue to see a shift to programmatic buying which presents opportunities for advertisers to connect with the right user, in the right moment, in the right context.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Programmatic buying has a different monetization profile than traditional advertising buying on Google properties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: •Users are increasingly using multiple devices and modalities to access our products and services, and our advertising revenues are increasingly coming from mobile and other new formats.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our users are accessing the Internet via multiple devices and modalities and want to feel connected no matter where they are or what they are doing.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We seek to expand our products and services to stay in front of this shift in order to maintain and grow our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generate our advertising revenues increasingly from mobile and newer advertising formats, and the margins from the advertising revenues from these sources have generally been lower than those from traditional desktop search.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Accordingly, we expect TAC paid to our distribution partners to increase due to changes in device mix between mobile, desktop, and tablet, partner mix, partner agreement terms, and the percentage of queries channeled through paid access points.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We expect these trends to continue to put pressure on our overall margins.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: •As users in developing economies increasingly come online, our revenues from international markets continue to increase and movements in foreign exchange rates impact such revenues.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The shift to online, as well as the advent of the multi-device world, has brought opportunities outside of the U.S., including in emerging markets, and we continue to develop localized versions of our products and relevant advertising programs useful to our users in these markets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This has led to a trend of increased revenues from international markets over time and we expect that our results will continue to be impacted by our performance in these markets, particularly as low-cost mobile devices become more available.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our international revenues represent a significant portion of our revenues and are subject to fluctuations in foreign currency exchange rates relative to the U.S. dollar.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: While we have a foreign exchange risk management program designed to reduce our exposure to these fluctuations, this program does not fully offset their effect on our revenues and earnings.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: •The portion of our revenues that we derive from non-advertising revenues is increasing and may impact margins.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Non-advertising revenues have grown over time.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We expect this trend to continue as we focus on expanding our offerings to our users through products and services like Google Cloud, Google Play, hardware products, and YouTube subscriptions.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Across these initiatives, we currently derive non-advertising revenues primarily from sales of apps, in-app purchases, digital content products, and hardware; and licensing and service fees including fees received for Google Cloud offerings.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The margins on these non-advertising businesses vary significantly and may be lower than the margins on our advertising business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: A number of our Other Bets initiatives are in their initial development stages, and as such, the sources of revenues from these businesses could change over time and the revenues could be volatile.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: •As we continue to look for new ways to serve our users and expand our businesses, we will invest heavily in R&D and our capital expenditures will continue to fluctuate.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to make significant research and development (R&D) investments in areas of strategic focus such as advertising, cloud, machine learning, and search, as well as in new products and services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The amount of our capital expenditures has fluctuated and may continue to fluctuate in the long term as we invest heavily in our systems, data centers, real estate and facilities, and information technology infrastructure.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, acquisitions remain an important part of our strategy and use of capital, and we expect to continue to spend cash on acquisitions and other investments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These acquisitions generally enhance the breadth and depth of our offerings, as well as expand our expertise in engineering and other functional areas.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our employees are critical to our success and we expect to continue investing in them.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our employees are among our best assets and are critical for our continued success.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Their energy and talent drive Alphabet and create our success.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We expect to continue hiring talented employees around the globe and to provide competitive compensation programs to our employees.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Executive Overview of Results Below are our key financial results for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2017 (consolidated unless otherwise noted):

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Revenues of $110.9 billion and revenue growth of 23% year over year, constant currency revenue growth of 24% year over year.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Google segment revenues of $109.7 billion with revenue growth of 23% year over year and Other Bets revenues of $1.2 billion with revenue growth of 49% year over year.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Revenues from the United States, EMEA, APAC, and Other Americas were $52.4 billion, $36.0 billion, $16.2 billion, and $6.1 billion, respectively.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Cost of revenues was $45.6 billion, consisting of TAC of $21.7 billion and other cost of revenues of $23.9 billion. Our TAC as a percentage of advertising revenues was 23%.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Operating expenses (excluding cost of revenues) were $39.1 billion.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Income from operations was $26.1 billion.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Effective tax rate was 53%.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Net income was $12.7 billion with diluted net income per share of $18.00.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Operating cash flow was $37.1 billion.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Capital expenditures were $13.2 billion.

sentence: • Number of employees was 80,110 as of December 31, 2017.

sentence: Information about Segments We operate our business in multiple operating segments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google is our only reportable segment.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: None of our other segments meet the quantitative thresholds to qualify as reportable segments; therefore, the other operating segments are combined and disclosed below as Other Bets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our reported segments are: • Google - Google includes our main products such as Ads, Android, Chrome, Commerce, Google Cloud, Google Maps, Google Play, Hardware, Search, and YouTube.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our technical infrastructure and some newer efforts like virtual reality are also included in Google.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google generates revenues primarily from advertising; sales of apps, in-app purchases, digital content products, and hardware; and licensing and service fees, including fees received for Google Cloud offerings.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Other Bets - Other Bets is a combination of multiple operating segments that are not individually material.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other Bets includes businesses such as Access, Calico, CapitalG, GV, Nest, Verily, Waymo, and X.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Revenues from the Other Bets are derived primarily through the sales of internet and TV services through Fiber, sales of Nest products and services, and licensing and R&D services through Verily.
